<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>35609</anchor> <rss>karlcrary.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Person</taxon> <addr>karlcrary</addr>  <route>karlcrary.xml</route>   <title>Karl Crary</title> <meta name="institution"><link href="cmu.xml" type="local" addr="cmu" title="Carnegie Mellon University">Carnegie Mellon University</link></meta><meta name="position">Professor</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter/> <backmatter><contributions><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>35610</anchor> <rss>jms-009L.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Letter</taxon> <addr>jms-009L</addr>  <route>jms-009L.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>9</month> <day>22</day></date> <authors><author><link href="karlcrary.xml" type="local" karlcrary="addr">Karl Crary</link></author> </authors> <title>Edmund M. Clarke Dissertation Award</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Dear friends,</p><p>I am delighted to announce that <link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" addr="jonmsterling" title="Jon Sterling">Jonathan Sterling</link> has been selected as the winner of the 2022 Edmund M. Clarke Dissertation Award in CSD for his thesis:</p><p><link href="sterling-2021-thesis.xml" type="local" addr="sterling-2021-thesis" title="First steps in synthetic Tait computability: the objective metatheory of cubical type theory">First Steps in Synthetic Tait Computability</link>, October 2021</p><p><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" addr="jonmsterling" title="Jon Sterling">Jonathan</link>’s PhD research was advised by <link href="robertharper.xml" type="local" addr="robertharper" title="Robert Harper">Robert Harper</link>.</p><p>This award, endowed by a generous contribution from Professor Ed Clarke and his wife Martha, is given annually to an outstanding dissertation in the Computer Science Department.</p><p>Congratulations <link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" addr="jonmsterling" title="Jon Sterling">Jonathan</link>!</p></mainmatter> </tree></contributions> <context/> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>35611</anchor> <rss>cmu.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Institution</taxon> <addr>cmu</addr>  <route>cmu.xml</route>   <title>Carnegie Mellon University</title> <meta name="external">https://www.cmu.edu/</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter/> </tree></related> <backlinks/> <references/></backmatter></tree>